---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
		title="About Me"
		description="UI/UX at IDS, Maker, and Problem Solver."
		pubDate={new Date('March 09 2026')}
>
	<p class="tagline">
		Senior UI Developer and UX Designer by day. Maker by... everything else.
	</p>

	<section class="bio">
		<p>
			I currently work at <strong>Integrated Data Services</strong>.
			My day job is building enterprise apps with
			<strong>Angular</strong>, <strong>SCSS</strong>, and <strong>Bootstrap</strong>.
		</p>

		<p>
			I tend to build things out of spite. If a workflow annoys me enough, I end up trying to come up with a solution to fix it.
		</p>

		<p>
			When I’m away from the screen, I’m still making things. I am an artist at heart and love working in a variety of media (stained glass, painting, ceramics).
		</p>

	</section>

	<style>
        .tagline {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            line-height: 1.3;
            color: var(--black);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }
        .bio p {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            line-height: 1.7;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }
        strong {
            color: var(--accent);
        }
	</style>
</Layout>